SOFIA
So what, do you just write prose, like a lot of notes?

ANTIPHON
Nah, each event has prose and some details, so 1950 is a date, father is a name of that event, and mother is the name of some other event. I can hide prose under "is...", details under "with..." and lists under "and...". It reads like a sentence. I will show the type of each thing in brackets for now.
```txt
father(event) is: Father was born(prose) with: 1950(date)
me(event) is: I was born(prose) with: 1990(date) father(name) and: mother(name)
// same hidden
me(event) is... with...
granma-story(event) is: Granma told me about the winter of 1943. She said the river froze.(prose) with: 2023-05-17(date) granma(name)
```

SOFIA
So you have a list of these sentences.

ANTIPHON
Nah, I need to connect them to each other. I put one event in the center, everything it references to left, and everything that references it to the right. I can click on father and see father's center instead.
```
father is... with: 1950
________me is: I was born with: 1990
mother is... with: 1951
// choose father
granma is... with: 1925   me is... with...
________father is... with: 1950
__________________________brother is... with...
```

